article.headline: Indiana 67, Wright St. 44
article.story: BLOOMINGTON, Ind. -- Verdell Jones scored 12 of Indiana's first 18 points and finished with 27 to lead the Hoosiers to a 67-44 victory over Wright State on Sunday night. Christian Watford added 17 points and 10 rebounds for the Hoosiers (2-0). Vaughn Duggins scored 15 points for Wright State in coach Billy Donlon's debut. Indiana led 30-19 at halftime, went up 37-21 two minutes into the second half, and Wright State never got closer than nine points the rest of the way. The Raiders took an early 9-4 lead, but the Hoosiers responded with a 15-1 run to gain control. Indiana dominated the rebounding 40-20.
